criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Type Ⅰ、Ⅱ、Ⅲ、Ⅳ of Hilar Cholangiocarcinoma;

          -  Age: 18~90 years old;

          -  Underwent diagnostic and therapeutic ERCP;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Coagulation dysfunction(INR＞1.3) or/and low peripheral blood platelet count （PLT
             <50x10^9/L）;

          -  Preoperative acute cholangitis;

          -  Preoperative acute pancreatitis;

          -  Preoperative hemobilia or hemorrhage of digestive tract;

          -  Preoperative liver failure;

          -  Combined with Mirizzi syndrome and intrahepatic bile duct stones;

          -  Preoperative malignant tumor of biliary system such as carcinoma of head of pancreas,
             gallbladder carcinoma;

          -  Biliary-duodenal fistula confirmed during ERCP;

          -  A history of reconstructive surgery for upper digestive tract except Billroth Ⅰand a
             history of cholangioenterostomy including cholangio-jejunostomy and side to side
             anastomosis of the bile duct and duodenum;

          -  Previous ERCP;

          -  Pregnant women
